*please note that our naming terminology will follow camelCase convention for example letsGoForOurProject

*a boolean variable should first start with "is" keyword
ex: isVisitor

*a controller should start with a small letter and end with "CTRL" all letters are capitalized 
ex: userCTRL

*all view files shoud start with a small letter

*all model files shoud start with a capital letter

*all variables and methods should start with a small letter

*all routings will follow the underscore terminology
ex: /main_page

*all exported database schemas should start with capital letter
ex: 
var Portfolio = mongoose.model("portfolio", portfolioSchema);
module.exports = Portfolio;

*for database namings:
Singular names for single variables. ex: age
Plural names for arrays. ex: offeredActivities


